What does a "Diamond" customer mean to Progressive

I have bundled my auto, home, and umbrella policies with Progressive. I've been with Progressive for over 5 years and have received a "Diamond" rating. My auto policy renews every six months, and I have a credit card on file for auto-renewal. This month, Progressive was unable to process a payment because the credit card on file was replaced by a new one due to fraudulent activities. Shawn, the representative, mentioned that the system generated an email to notify me that the card was declined. I did not receive that email, but I did receive an email today that my policy had lapsed. I logged on today and made a payment. When I made the payment, I noticed that Progressive added an additional $30 surcharge for a six-month auto policy with a one-day lapse in coverage. Shawn told me the reason for this increase is due to the lower rating that the system generated because of the one-day lapse in payment. Even though I mentioned that I did not receive a notification that my card was declined, he would do nothing to remedy the situation. Lower ratings usually mean higher premiums. So much for being a loyal Progressive customer and trusting them with my auto, home, and umbrella policies.
